---
import MainLayout from "../../layouts/main.astro";
---

<MainLayout class="contentContainer">
  <article class="termsContent">
    <section class="header">
      <h1>Community Guidelines</h1>
      <p class="lastUpdatedDate">Last updated: 17 July 2026</p>
    </section>

    <section class="termsBody">
      <p>RTS exists to help people find useful websites, articles, and online resources.</p>
      <p>
        These guidelines explain what kind of community we want to build. They are not meant to cover every possible situation. Moderators
        will always use their best judgment to keep RTS helpful, respectful, and welcoming.
      </p>
      <p>Following these guidelines is required when using RTS.</p>

      <h2>1. Be Respectful</h2>
      <p>Treat other people with respect.</p>
      <p>Disagreements are normal. Personal attacks are not.</p>
      <p>Do not:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>insult, harass, or threaten others;</li>
        <li>encourage targeted harassment;</li>
        <li>discriminate against people based on protected characteristics;</li>
        <li>deliberately provoke arguments or start conflicts.</li>
      </ul>
      <p>Discuss ideas. Do not attack people.</p>

      <h2>2. Keep Reviews Helpful</h2>
      <p>Reviews should help other people.</p>
      <p>A good review explains your experience and gives useful information.</p>
      <p>Examples of helpful reviews:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>what worked well;</li>
        <li>what did not work;</li>
        <li>who the website is useful for;</li>
        <li>whether the information is accurate;</li>
        <li>whether the website is safe to use.</li>
      </ul>
      <p>Avoid reviews that only contain insults, profanity, or unrelated comments.</p>

      <h2>3. Submit Useful Resources</h2>
      <p>Only submit resources that provide real value.</p>
      <p>We welcome:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>educational websites;</li>
        <li>documentation;</li>
        <li>tutorials;</li>
        <li>articles;</li>
        <li>developer tools;</li>
        <li>open source projects;</li>
        <li>calculators;</li>
        <li>communities;</li>
        <li>reference material.</li>
      </ul>
      <p>We may reject submissions that exist only to advertise products or services.</p>

      <h2>4. Keep Information Accurate</h2>
      <p>Do not knowingly submit false or misleading information.</p>
      <p>If information becomes outdated, help improve it by suggesting updates or reporting the issue.</p>

      <h2>5. No Spam</h2>
      <p>Spam makes RTS less useful.</p>
      <p>Do not:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>repeatedly submit the same resource;</li>
        <li>post unrelated reviews;</li>
        <li>advertise your own projects excessively;</li>
        <li>create multiple accounts to manipulate ratings or discussions;</li>
        <li>use automated tools to submit content without permission.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>6. Illegal or Harmful Content</h2>
      <p>Do not submit or promote content involving:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>malware;</li>
        <li>phishing;</li>
        <li>scams;</li>
        <li>copyright infringement;</li>
        <li>illegal activity;</li>
        <li>terrorism or violent extremism;</li>
        <li>child sexual abuse material;</li>
        <li>instructions intended to harm others.</li>
      </ul>
      <p>Content that puts users at risk will be removed immediately.</p>

      <h2>7. Adult Content</h2>
      <p>RTS is intended to be safe for a general audience.</p>
      <p>Do not submit or promote websites whose primary purpose is explicit sexual content.</p>
      <p>Educational, medical, or scientific resources discussing sexual health are allowed when presented appropriately.</p>

      <h2>8. Privacy</h2>
      <p>Respect the privacy of others.</p>
      <p>Do not publish personal information without permission.</p>
      <p>Examples include:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>home addresses;</li>
        <li>phone numbers;</li>
        <li>email addresses;</li>
        <li>government identification numbers;</li>
        <li>private conversations;</li>
        <li>financial information.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>9. Copyright</h2>
      <p>Only submit content that you have the right to share.</p>
      <p>When quoting or referencing another source, give proper credit where appropriate.</p>
      <p>If you believe your copyright has been infringed, contact us and we will review your report.</p>

      <h2>10. Security</h2>
      <p>Do not attempt to:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>gain unauthorized access to RTS;</li>
        <li>bypass security measures;</li>
        <li>exploit software vulnerabilities;</li>
        <li>interfere with the Service;</li>
        <li>overload our infrastructure.</li>
      </ul>
      <p>If you discover a security issue, please report it responsibly instead of exploiting it.</p>

      <h2>11. Moderation</h2>
      <p>Moderators enforce these guidelines to protect the community.</p>
      <p>Moderators may:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>approve or reject submissions;</li>
        <li>remove content;</li>
        <li>suspend or ban accounts;</li>
        <li>lock discussions;</li>
        <li>take other reasonable actions when necessary.</li>
      </ul>
      <p>Moderators aim to make decisions fairly, consistently, and in good faith.</p>

      <h2>12. Appeals</h2>
      <p>If you believe a moderation decision was incorrect, you are welcome to appeal.</p>
      <p>Please explain why you believe the decision should be reviewed.</p>
      <p>Be respectful.</p>
      <p>Repeated appeals about the same decision may not receive another review.</p>

      <h2>13. Help Improve RTS</h2>
      <p>RTS is an open source project built with help from its community.</p>
      <p>You can help by:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>reporting bugs;</li>
        <li>suggesting useful resources;</li>
        <li>improving inaccurate information;</li>
        <li>reporting rule violations;</li>
        <li>contributing to the open source project;</li>
        <li>sharing constructive feedback.</li>
      </ul>
      <p>A helpful community is more valuable than a large one.</p>
      <p>
        Thank you for helping make RTS a place where people can find useful information without spam, misleading content, or unnecessary
        noise.
      </p>
    </section>
  </article>
</MainLayout>

<style lang="scss">
  .contentContainer {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    padding: 0;
  }

  .termsContent {
    width: 100%;
    max-width: var(--max-content-width);
    padding: 0 20px;

    .header {
      display: flex;
      flex-direction: column;
      justify-content: center;
      align-items: flex-start;
      height: auto;
      padding: 70px 0;

      h1 {
        color: var(--text);
        font-size: 48px;
        font-style: normal;
        font-weight: 600;
        line-height: normal;
        text-align: left;
        width: 100%;
        margin: 0 0 20px 0;
      }

      .lastUpdatedDate {
        text-align: left;
        width: 100%;
        font-size: 14px;
        color: var(--dimmed-text-two);
        padding: 0;
        margin: 0;
      }
    }

    .termsBody {
      display: flex;
      flex-direction: column;
      gap: 20px;
      padding-bottom: 100px;

      p {
        color: var(--text);
        font-size: 16px;
        line-height: 1.6;
        margin: 0;

        a {
          color: var(--text);
          text-decoration: underline;
          transition: opacity 0.2s ease;

          &:hover {
            opacity: 0.7;
          }
        }
      }

      h2 {
        color: var(--text);
        font-size: 24px;
        font-style: normal;
        font-weight: 600;
        line-height: normal;
        margin: 0;
        padding: 0 0 0 16px;
        border-left: 4px solid var(--text);
        opacity: 0.8;
      }

      h3 {
        color: var(--text);
        font-size: 20px;
        font-style: normal;
        font-weight: 600;
        line-height: normal;
        margin: 0;
        padding: 0 0 0 12px;
        border-left: 2px solid var(--text);
        opacity: 0.8;
      }

      ul {
        list-style: none;
        padding-left: 20px;
        margin: 0;

        li {
          color: var(--text);
          font-size: 16px;
          line-height: 1.6;
          margin-bottom: 10px;
          position: relative;
          padding-left: 15px;

          &::before {
            content: "•";
            position: absolute;
            left: 0;
            font-weight: bold;
          }
        }
      }
    }
  }

  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .termsContent {
      .header {
        padding: 40px 0;

        h1 {
          font-size: 32px;
        }

        .lastUpdatedDate {
          font-size: 12px;
        }
      }

      .termsBody {
        gap: 16px;
        padding-bottom: 50px;

        p {
          font-size: 14px;
        }

        h2 {
          font-size: 20px;
        }

        h3 {
          font-size: 17px;
        }

        ul li {
          font-size: 14px;
        }
      }
    }
  }
</style>
